CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 5, 1955, pg. 14A, reads: " 'Bye, Bye, Mr. McKinney!' - Saddened youngsters of Hill City bid farewell to their late friend and leader, Howard C. McKinney, as the deceased's body was carried from Central Baptist Church to the hearse last Saturday, for its last ride-to the cemetery. Mr. McKinney was a prime favorite to Hill District youngsters of all races. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Crowd of young women, and men, some wearing Hill City marching band uniforms, standing on brick herringbone patterned sidewalk for Howard C. McKinney funeral procession, Hill District
